00:04:28.440 --> 00:04:34.440
[Guest]: Yeah yeah for the longest time before I got into comedy I spent from my board exams that were done

00:04:34.440 --> 00:04:37.440
[Guest]: At 16 to like 23 I was just hosting events

00:04:37.440 --> 00:04:44.440
[Guest]: Like you know comparing birthday parties, baptisms, communions, weddings, engagement all kinds of shit

00:04:44.440 --> 00:04:47.440
[Guest]: Like you know I was always the guy there you know like and leading it

00:04:47.440 --> 00:04:50.440
[Guest]: Not only just being a master of ceremony for the heck of it

00:04:50.440 --> 00:04:53.440
[Guest]: I would like sit down with the family, plan together

00:04:53.440 --> 00:04:57.440
[Guest]: And there were ladies in my church would see me working for the church

00:04:57.440 --> 00:05:00.440
[Guest]: And they would like have dreams about me becoming a priest one day

00:05:00.440 --> 00:05:02.440
[Guest]: Like that was intensely what they believed in

00:05:02.440 --> 00:05:04.440
[Guest]: And then some of them would die the next month and my mom would be like

00:05:04.440 --> 00:05:08.440
[Guest]: Oh they were like really having prophetic thoughts because they were going to pass away soon

00:05:08.440 --> 00:05:09.440
[Guest]: I'm like mom calm down

00:05:09.440 --> 00:05:13.440
[Guest]: But at the age of 13 I was genuinely interested in going for the church

00:05:13.440 --> 00:05:17.440
[Guest]: Because at around the same time I realized what my orientation was

00:05:17.440 --> 00:05:21.440
[Guest]: And at the same time you know like everybody around me was so Catholic

00:05:21.440 --> 00:05:23.440
[Guest]: And we had such blinders on

00:05:23.440 --> 00:05:28.440
[Guest]: I kind of believed that this is my destiny because if God did not want me to be like a married man

00:05:28.440 --> 00:05:31.440
[Guest]: Then this is what he would give me to make me more in touch with him

00:05:31.440 --> 00:05:34.440
[Guest]: So I would spend more time in the church by default

00:05:34.440 --> 00:05:38.440
[Guest]: So all my skills from talking publicly to like being artistic in any kind of way

00:05:38.440 --> 00:05:41.440
[Guest]: Be it music or being in the choir

00:05:41.440 --> 00:05:46.440
[Guest]: It was all cultivated within the church but my world was only limited to that

00:05:46.440 --> 00:05:48.440
[Guest]: And that's when the whole first coming out phase happened

00:05:48.440 --> 00:05:51.440
[Guest]: Because I realized that there's a world outside

00:05:51.440 --> 00:05:54.440
[Guest]: Which is like you know if you go to the better suburbs like Bandra and Andheri

00:05:54.440 --> 00:05:59.440
[Guest]: There's an entire cultural hotspot that is being birthed and we are not a part of that

00:05:59.440 --> 00:06:03.440
[Guest]: So I would go to this place called Haivankar and you know do open mics over there

00:06:03.440 --> 00:06:07.440
[Guest]: And then by default meet more cooler people who were doing cool things you know

00:06:07.440 --> 00:06:10.440
[Guest]: There were poets, filmmakers, artists of all sorts

00:06:10.440 --> 00:06:15.440
[Guest]: And within this the first proper understanding happened of how much I was losing out

00:06:15.440 --> 00:06:18.440
[Guest]: By just being in a very small community of people who were just like you know

00:06:18.440 --> 00:06:22.440
[Guest]: Whenever you did something nice they patted you on the back but where would that lead to?

00:06:22.440 --> 00:06:27.440
[Guest]: And in that understanding I learned more about what the church was not telling us you know

00:06:27.440 --> 00:06:32.440
[Guest]: The whole pedophilia racket and what was happening back in our own playground

00:06:32.440 --> 00:06:35.440
[Guest]: And my mom and I would have vehement arguments about that

00:06:35.440 --> 00:06:39.440
[Guest]: So hence the concern of like ever coming to terms with my orientation

00:06:39.440 --> 00:06:44.440
[Guest]: Was diminished because of the fact that I grew up in such a staunch community that would never accept me

00:06:44.440 --> 00:06:49.440
[Guest]: And hence the walking away from the church happened like a little more drastically than I imagined

00:06:49.440 --> 00:06:50.440
[Guest]: But it had to happen I feel

00:06:50.440 --> 00:06:53.440
[Amit Varma]: But so take me a little back earlier in your childhood

00:06:53.440 --> 00:06:58.440
[Amit Varma]: And again I should apologize in advance if my questions seem very ignorant or insensitive in any way

00:06:58.440 --> 00:07:01.440
[Amit Varma]: Because I'm just coming from a position of pure curiosity

00:07:01.440 --> 00:07:06.440
[Amit Varma]: And also you grew up in a different time than you know I'm a fair bit older than you

00:07:06.440 --> 00:07:09.440
[Amit Varma]: And you're 26, I'm 44, I grew up in a different time

00:07:09.440 --> 00:07:12.440
[Amit Varma]: So and it's very hard for me to sort of imagine your childhood

00:07:12.440 --> 00:07:15.440
[Amit Varma]: So growing up as a young person in Bhaindar

00:07:15.440 --> 00:07:20.440
[Amit Varma]: At a time where you didn't have so much access to the media and the internet

00:07:20.440 --> 00:07:22.440
[Amit Varma]: And so much of gay culture coming in

00:07:22.440 --> 00:07:23.440
[Guest]: Exactly

00:07:23.440 --> 00:07:28.440
[Amit Varma]: How was it that like what was the process like of discovering that you're gay

00:07:28.440 --> 00:07:30.440
[Amit Varma]: And then how do you come to terms with those feelings?

00:07:30.440 --> 00:07:33.440
[Guest]: I was always a loner kid per se

00:07:33.440 --> 00:07:35.440
[Guest]: Like when we moved, we moved a lot of houses when I was younger

00:07:35.440 --> 00:07:39.440
[Guest]: Because my parents are first generation immigrants to Bombay

00:07:39.440 --> 00:07:41.440
[Guest]: So we just had to like move and find our own place

00:07:41.440 --> 00:07:43.440
[Guest]: So when we finally got our own apartment

00:07:43.440 --> 00:07:45.440
[Guest]: We moved to Bhaindar and I was like 7

00:07:45.440 --> 00:07:50.440
[Guest]: And a lot of friendships happened within the kindergarten to like the first 3 years of schooling

00:07:50.440 --> 00:07:53.440
[Guest]: And the last like later years because you're friends in school

00:07:53.440 --> 00:07:55.440
[Guest]: But I didn't have any of those friends

00:07:55.440 --> 00:07:57.440
[Amit Varma]: And this would be like 1999-2000

00:07:57.440 --> 00:07:58.440
[Guest]: 1998 yeah

00:07:58.440 --> 00:08:01.440
[Guest]: So 1999 when we were like really properly settled down

00:08:01.440 --> 00:08:03.440
[Guest]: My sisters were much older than me

00:08:03.440 --> 00:08:06.440
[Guest]: So they would go to college and my mom and dad were both like working really hard

00:08:06.440 --> 00:08:08.440
[Guest]: To like make sure we could make ends meet

00:08:08.440 --> 00:08:10.440
[Guest]: So I was left alone in my own imaginary world

00:08:10.440 --> 00:08:13.440
[Guest]: So like you know in a very Andy Kaufman-esque style

00:08:13.440 --> 00:08:15.440
[Guest]: I would sit against the bed, look at the wall

00:08:15.440 --> 00:08:18.440
[Guest]: And make my own you know like pictures and everything

00:08:18.440 --> 00:08:23.440
[Guest]: So I was always into like creating drama and art and everything

00:08:23.440 --> 00:08:25.440
[Guest]: In my own head I would write scripts and everything

00:08:25.440 --> 00:08:28.440
[Guest]: I still got those scribble little notes of like my handwriting

00:08:28.440 --> 00:08:32.440
[Guest]: I would read Tinkle comics and then try to adapt those stories to like real life

00:08:32.440 --> 00:08:35.440
[Guest]: So all of that was like you know a small part of my life

00:08:35.440 --> 00:08:39.440
[Guest]: And I had very good friends who would play like imaginary friends with me as well at the same time

00:08:39.440 --> 00:08:41.440
[Guest]: So very close circuit

00:08:41.440 --> 00:08:46.440
[Guest]: I lost one of my really dear friends to like a spinal problem that he had

00:08:46.440 --> 00:08:49.440
[Guest]: And since then I became a little more detached

00:08:49.440 --> 00:08:51.440
[Guest]: So we were three of us very close to each other

00:08:51.440 --> 00:08:53.440
[Guest]: And one of them moved to Russia

00:08:53.440 --> 00:08:54.440
[Guest]: And one of them passed away

00:08:54.440 --> 00:08:57.440
[Guest]: So like I felt like a lot of my life was going to be

00:08:57.440 --> 00:08:59.440
[Guest]: Losing friends on different levels

00:08:59.440 --> 00:09:02.440
[Guest]: And that kind of is also a very common theme across my life

00:09:02.440 --> 00:09:05.440
[Guest]: That I become close to people and they either move out, move away

00:09:05.440 --> 00:09:08.440
[Guest]: Or just like stop existing sometimes

00:09:08.440 --> 00:09:10.440
[Guest]: So I've dealt with that kind of thing you know

00:09:10.440 --> 00:09:12.440
[Guest]: Like why make friends or why make family

00:09:12.440 --> 00:09:14.440
[Guest]: When they're all going to just like walk away from you

00:09:14.440 --> 00:09:17.440
[Guest]: So it became easy for me when I grew up to like

00:09:17.440 --> 00:09:20.440
[Guest]: Detach myself in the whole coming out phase

00:09:20.440 --> 00:09:23.440
[Guest]: Because I just felt that there was a threshold I had reached

00:09:23.440 --> 00:09:29.440
[Guest]: And the whole emotional gush that happens when you're first understanding

00:09:29.440 --> 00:09:31.440
[Guest]: That you are feeling differently than the others

00:09:31.440 --> 00:09:33.440
[Guest]: You don't have anybody to tell you know

00:09:33.440 --> 00:09:35.440
[Guest]: Like as I joke about in my bit

00:09:35.440 --> 00:09:38.440
[Guest]: That I would go to the girls and we'd talk about Spice Girls and stuff like that

00:09:38.440 --> 00:09:41.440
[Guest]: At the same time the boys would try to show me straight porn

00:09:41.440 --> 00:09:43.440
[Guest]: And try to see if that works on me

00:09:43.440 --> 00:09:47.440
[Guest]: So it's like it was always a pendulum of being confused about what it is

00:09:47.440 --> 00:09:48.440
[Guest]: And why are they feeling differently

00:09:48.440 --> 00:09:50.440
[Guest]: Like you know like a boy and a girl would hold hands

00:09:50.440 --> 00:09:52.440
[Guest]: And I would want that but not with a girl

00:09:52.440 --> 00:09:55.440
[Guest]: You know like it's all kinds of weird thoughts and brainwaves

00:09:55.440 --> 00:09:57.440
[Guest]: That you don't know how to define

00:09:57.440 --> 00:10:01.440
[Guest]: And hence it's very important to understand at an early age

00:10:01.440 --> 00:10:04.440
[Guest]: And in my travels I've figured out that a lot of schools

00:10:04.440 --> 00:10:08.440
[Guest]: Not only just like better schools that are internationally controlled or whatever

00:10:08.440 --> 00:10:10.440
[Guest]: Even the low level schools that are state run

00:10:10.440 --> 00:10:14.440
[Guest]: Are now teaching kids about same sex relationships

00:10:14.440 --> 00:10:16.440
[Guest]: Which is important because if there was somebody out there

00:10:16.440 --> 00:10:19.440
[Guest]: Telling me it was okay back when I was 13 or 14

00:10:19.440 --> 00:10:20.440
[Guest]: It would have been cool

00:10:20.440 --> 00:10:22.440
[Guest]: I remember we did have a sex education class

00:10:22.440 --> 00:10:25.440
[Guest]: And my ma'am clearly said that you know like

00:10:25.440 --> 00:10:27.440
[Guest]: Because it's difficult to pass a hard stool

00:10:27.440 --> 00:10:29.440
[Guest]: Imagine how painful anal sex is

00:10:29.440 --> 00:10:31.440
[Guest]: And that's the only statement she said about gay sex

00:10:31.440 --> 00:10:34.440
[Guest]: And I'm just like scratching my head waiting

00:10:34.440 --> 00:10:37.440
[Guest]: Tell me more, I'm having all these feelings

00:10:37.440 --> 00:10:39.440
[Guest]: And nothing is being answered

00:10:39.440 --> 00:10:41.440
[Amit Varma]: She must have a raunchy life

00:10:41.440 --> 00:10:43.440
[Amit Varma]: So basically you didn't have a framework

00:10:43.440 --> 00:10:45.440
[Amit Varma]: Where you could put the way you were feeling

00:10:45.440 --> 00:10:48.440
[Amit Varma]: It was just that you were different and you couldn't understand why

00:10:48.440 --> 00:10:49.440
[Guest]: Nothing, nothing

00:10:49.440 --> 00:10:53.440
[Guest]: I was like told that there's a word for it called Baila

00:10:53.440 --> 00:10:55.440
[Guest]: Which is very commonly used in Bombay

00:10:55.440 --> 00:10:57.440
[Guest]: Baila is like womanesque

00:10:57.440 --> 00:10:59.440
[Guest]: So if you have a limp arm and if you behave a certain way

00:10:59.440 --> 00:11:01.440
[Guest]: If your hips are whatever

00:11:01.440 --> 00:11:03.440
[Guest]: You know if you do all of that

00:11:03.440 --> 00:11:05.440
[Guest]: And that's again the picture Bollywood paints

00:11:05.440 --> 00:11:06.440
[Unknown]: And we understand that

00:11:06.440 --> 00:11:08.440
[Guest]: I remember when I was younger

00:11:08.440 --> 00:11:12.440
[Guest]: I loved some of these movies that had a stereotypical gay character

00:11:12.440 --> 00:11:14.440
[Guest]: And I'm like I'm not relating to this either

00:11:14.440 --> 00:11:15.440
[Guest]: This is not me

00:11:15.440 --> 00:11:17.440
[Guest]: So what is this definition that I'm trying to find

00:11:17.440 --> 00:11:21.440
[Guest]: And hence getting access to Facebook and social media

00:11:21.440 --> 00:11:24.440
[Guest]: Became very handy around when I was 17 or 18

00:11:24.440 --> 00:11:27.440
[Guest]: I would go to cyber cafes and then sit and like you know

00:11:27.440 --> 00:11:28.440
[Guest]: Start looking up shit

00:11:28.440 --> 00:11:30.440
[Guest]: So on Awkward there were a lot of communities

00:11:30.440 --> 00:11:32.440
[Guest]: A lot of gay communities that would have like chat rooms

00:11:32.440 --> 00:11:34.440
[Guest]: And you couldn't talk to people who were counsellors

00:11:34.440 --> 00:11:35.440
[Guest]: Yahoo Messenger happened

00:11:35.440 --> 00:11:38.440
[Guest]: The whole ISL generation that we were exposed to

00:11:38.440 --> 00:11:42.440
[Guest]: Was really handy for like people who were gay to communicate with each other

00:11:42.440 --> 00:11:45.440
[Guest]: We sometimes look at internet as a very bad place

00:11:45.440 --> 00:11:47.440
[Guest]: Because of how you can you know fall in trouble

00:11:47.440 --> 00:11:49.440
[Guest]: But for a lot of gay youngsters

00:11:49.440 --> 00:11:51.440
[Guest]: It becomes a very key factor in determining who they are

00:11:51.440 --> 00:11:54.440
[Guest]: By talking to people who are the same you know

00:11:54.440 --> 00:11:56.440
[Guest]: Like I made a pseudo account on Facebook

00:11:56.440 --> 00:11:57.440
[Guest]: And I'm kind of proud of that

00:11:57.440 --> 00:12:01.440
[Guest]: Because I would like go and talk to people from UK, US, Australia

00:12:01.440 --> 00:12:03.440
[Guest]: Who were openly gay and you know

00:12:03.440 --> 00:12:05.440
[Guest]: They were not ashamed of who they were

00:12:05.440 --> 00:12:06.440
[Guest]: And they would talk to me about

00:12:06.440 --> 00:12:07.440
[Guest]: How they're settling down with their partners

00:12:07.440 --> 00:12:10.440
[Guest]: How marriages are still you know difficult to get in some parts

00:12:10.440 --> 00:12:12.440
[Guest]: How they're hoping to find licenses

00:12:12.440 --> 00:12:16.440
[Guest]: And all of that kind of inspired me to like then talk about it

00:12:16.440 --> 00:12:18.440
[Guest]: I remember because in the article I talk about

00:12:18.440 --> 00:12:20.440
