[Guest]: me some more money.

00:29:53.360 --> 00:29:57.440
[Guest]: So overall, I was like taking care of the house now slowly.

00:29:57.440 --> 00:30:02.160
[Guest]: And hence, like, there was still a certain level of attachment to the family.

00:30:02.160 --> 00:30:06.880
[Guest]: But they were constantly aware that I was not making as well and don't keep constantly,

00:30:06.880 --> 00:30:12.120
[Guest]: you know, planting it in my head again and again that, hey, if you were doing this would

00:30:12.120 --> 00:30:13.480
[Guest]: have been happier.

00:30:13.480 --> 00:30:14.480
[Guest]: Maybe you can go back to it.

00:30:14.480 --> 00:30:16.640
[Guest]: And I was like, no, I've left that life behind entirely.

00:30:16.640 --> 00:30:18.720
[Guest]: I was happy doing what I was doing.

00:30:18.720 --> 00:30:24.600
[Guest]: So it was like, for the longest time, I did not emote so much at home, which I also regret

00:30:24.600 --> 00:30:28.320
[Guest]: now because I could have been more abrupt about it.

00:30:28.320 --> 00:30:32.280
[Guest]: And, you know, like, I just tried to like, placate everybody at the same time and make

00:30:32.280 --> 00:30:34.480
[Guest]: sure I could hold all those things together.

00:30:34.480 --> 00:30:38.600
[Guest]: Because one of the main reasons coming out is difficult in India, because what if they

00:30:38.600 --> 00:30:41.520
[Guest]: throw me out and I have to like, then be on the streets.

00:30:41.520 --> 00:30:45.720
[Guest]: So I just have to make sure that I can make sure I can earn enough money at the same time

00:30:45.720 --> 00:30:51.080
[Guest]: and take care of myself if that whole phase happens when I have to go out.

00:30:51.080 --> 00:30:58.200
[Guest]: And then the second coming out happened around the same time because I was so away from the

00:30:58.200 --> 00:31:01.880
[Guest]: church for a while that I did not want to go back to it and, you know, be in the same

00:31:01.880 --> 00:31:07.480
[Guest]: environment with the same kind of homophobic because religion is kind of like very handy

00:31:07.480 --> 00:31:09.360
[Guest]: when it comes to homophobia.

00:31:09.360 --> 00:31:12.760
[Guest]: People start quoting lines and stuff like that, which I don't want to deal with.

00:31:12.760 --> 00:31:18.160
[Guest]: So proactively, I stopped going to church and that was a very hateful period in my house

00:31:18.160 --> 00:31:20.080
[Guest]: because they could not take that at all.

00:31:20.080 --> 00:31:25.440
[Guest]: Like, you know, I was raised in such a strong household that for me, not going to church

00:31:25.440 --> 00:31:28.080
[Guest]: was like the biggest sin I'd ever committed in my entire life.

00:31:28.080 --> 00:31:32.360
[Amit Varma]: And looking back retrospectively, would you say you were ever a believer in God per se

00:31:32.360 --> 00:31:36.800
[Amit Varma]: or you got so involved in the church because of the community and cultural aspects of it?

00:31:36.800 --> 00:31:37.800
[Guest]: That's the latter.

00:31:37.800 --> 00:31:42.880
[Guest]: I think like we eventually end up saying that we believe in God and we love him and everything.

00:31:42.880 --> 00:31:46.520
[Guest]: But older I grew, obviously, there was a more sense of, oh, wait, like, what if there's

00:31:46.520 --> 00:31:49.240
[Guest]: a supreme being that we don't know how to put a name to?

00:31:49.240 --> 00:31:51.880
[Guest]: And then you will see all the killings that are happening in the name of religion and

00:31:51.880 --> 00:31:56.080
[Guest]: you know, you read a little bit and you understand that, oh, all of this is kind of made up and

00:31:56.080 --> 00:31:58.120
[Guest]: the crusades happened.

00:31:58.120 --> 00:32:02.160
[Guest]: So you know, like when you would think about all of these things, you'd be like, oh, wait,

00:32:02.160 --> 00:32:06.640
[Guest]: like let's take a backtracking mechanism here and be like, the main reason you liked it

00:32:06.640 --> 00:32:11.040
[Guest]: so much because everybody's just like so into you and they all praise you and they all want

00:32:11.040 --> 00:32:13.760
[Guest]: to make the best out of what they're given sort of.

00:32:13.760 --> 00:32:17.800
[Guest]: So like our church annual parties and, you know, family gatherings and all that were

00:32:17.800 --> 00:32:22.600
[Guest]: like pretty famous because you'd pay 60 bucks and then get a raffle ticket for Easter and

00:32:22.600 --> 00:32:25.080
[Guest]: at the same time eat free biryani and shit like that.

00:32:25.080 --> 00:32:28.560
[Guest]: So they keep you in the system like that, you know, don't call free biryani shit like

00:32:28.560 --> 00:32:29.560
[Guest]: that.

00:32:29.560 --> 00:32:32.560
[Guest]: Oh, I've been on a keto diet all of this year, I'd do anything for a biryani.

00:32:32.560 --> 00:32:33.560
[Guest]: Oh, me too.

00:32:33.560 --> 00:32:36.960
[Amit Varma]: I'm going tonight to have somebody, I'm afraid I can't.

00:32:36.960 --> 00:32:37.960
[Guest]: Don't send me pictures.

00:32:37.960 --> 00:32:40.240
[Guest]: It'll be on Instagram tomorrow morning.

00:32:40.240 --> 00:32:43.320
[Amit Varma]: I don't follow you on Instagram anymore.

00:32:43.320 --> 00:32:45.720
[Guest]: So yeah, it was good to have that system.

00:32:45.720 --> 00:32:51.120
[Guest]: But you know, I yearned for more, as I said, like, it's just it's so much easier to understand

00:32:51.120 --> 00:32:55.720
[Guest]: that sometimes all the hard work you do has a payoff, instead of people subverting you

00:32:55.720 --> 00:32:57.760
[Guest]: and telling you you're doing a good job.

00:32:57.760 --> 00:33:02.640
[Guest]: So when I start deviating from the church, it was really difficult for my family to digest

00:33:02.640 --> 00:33:08.160
[Guest]: the fact by default, like it was, it was like the biggest travesty and I was so now like

00:33:08.160 --> 00:33:09.160
[Amit Varma]: nobody's business.

00:33:09.160 --> 00:33:12.720
[Amit Varma]: Is there a moment where you announced to them that there is a clean cut between you and

00:33:12.720 --> 00:33:14.520
[Guest]: the church or an atheist now?

00:33:14.520 --> 00:33:18.880
[Guest]: There was like my mom and my sister were at home and they were trying to like really argue

00:33:18.880 --> 00:33:21.920
[Guest]: and debate about why I'm not believing in all of this.

00:33:21.920 --> 00:33:25.000
[Guest]: Like I would not even step out of my room when they would start praying and my family

00:33:25.000 --> 00:33:31.840
[Guest]: is such for like 30 minutes before the midnight, before dinner every night, we spent 30 minutes

00:33:31.840 --> 00:33:35.120
[Guest]: praying like, you know, kneeling down and raising our hands in the air kind of like

00:33:35.120 --> 00:33:36.740
[Guest]: crazy stuff.

00:33:36.740 --> 00:33:40.480
[Guest]: So I would just like stop participating in that and my sister was like, tell me why?

00:33:40.480 --> 00:33:44.840
[Guest]: And I'd be like, look at the whole way it's skewed and look at all this pedophilia and

00:33:44.840 --> 00:33:49.040
[Guest]: look at all how the church is, you know, like taking money from people, not helping them,

00:33:49.040 --> 00:33:50.040
[Guest]: all of that.

00:33:50.040 --> 00:33:53.560
[Guest]: Like, why is there so much disparity in African kids and Indian kids, we are so entitled,

00:33:53.560 --> 00:33:54.800
[Guest]: all of that.

00:33:54.800 --> 00:33:59.680
[Guest]: And my mom was like, just like for, for like five days more, go to church and try it out.

00:33:59.680 --> 00:34:03.720
[Guest]: I'm like, for five days, mom, you try to be an atheist, you stop believing in God and

00:34:03.720 --> 00:34:04.720
[Guest]: stop going to church.

00:34:04.720 --> 00:34:07.120
[Guest]: So like, how can you make me do something I don't want to do?

00:34:07.120 --> 00:34:10.360
[Guest]: And I'm like, touche, right now, that's what exactly what's happening.

00:34:10.360 --> 00:34:13.400
[Guest]: And she was like, oh, wait, then she actually took a step back and she realized she was

00:34:13.400 --> 00:34:17.480
[Guest]: doing the same thing to me, which I wanted her to do for a change.

00:34:17.480 --> 00:34:20.640
[Guest]: And then she was a little more calmer after that, she was like, okay, I think it's your

00:34:20.640 --> 00:34:21.640
[Guest]: call.

00:34:21.640 --> 00:34:25.200
[Guest]: But my dad, again, like my dad always goes to the extreme, does not exactly, he does

00:34:25.200 --> 00:34:29.880
[Guest]: not talk to me, talk to me, but also does not, like, he pulls the strings from the background,

00:34:29.880 --> 00:34:33.960
[Guest]: basically, he'll talk to my mom about something and he'll surnow her, and then her head is

00:34:33.960 --> 00:34:36.600
[Guest]: hurting because of my dad constantly, you know, bickering with her.

00:34:36.600 --> 00:34:40.400
[Guest]: So I was feeling like I'm causing all this stress in my family, I might as well move

00:34:40.400 --> 00:34:43.880
[Guest]: out now itself, because it's easier to like, just vanish from their lives.

00:34:43.880 --> 00:34:49.120
[Guest]: Again, a very stupid, impulsive teenage decision, I'm not even a teenager back then, I was 23.

00:34:49.120 --> 00:34:53.400
[Guest]: But I felt like going away from the house for some time would have been helpful.

00:34:53.400 --> 00:34:57.800
[Guest]: But that did not help at all, like they were crying more than they were usually doing that.

00:34:57.800 --> 00:35:01.600
[Guest]: And my dad would like, my dad picked up his phone and called me and I knew like shit's

00:35:01.600 --> 00:35:04.240
[Guest]: going down because he hardly calls me.

00:35:04.240 --> 00:35:09.320
[Guest]: And he's like, you've just like, gone and haven't told us where you are and what's happening.

00:35:09.320 --> 00:35:11.920
[Guest]: So after like 15 days, I finally got back home.

00:35:11.920 --> 00:35:15.040
[Guest]: And that's when I sat my mom down and I told her first.

00:35:15.040 --> 00:35:19.040
[Guest]: And there was a plan in action where it was like her birthday approaching, so we would

00:35:19.040 --> 00:35:22.140
[Guest]: not tell the entire family until her birthday.

00:35:22.140 --> 00:35:26.680
[Guest]: So we could like keep this between mother and son and then slowly tell the rest of the

00:35:26.680 --> 00:35:30.560
[Guest]: family in a more civilized manner when they all gathered together.

00:35:30.560 --> 00:35:34.320
[Guest]: So I could also do my piece and be like, hey, let me decentralize you, instead of you all

00:35:34.320 --> 00:35:36.680
[Guest]: just like assuming things.

00:35:36.680 --> 00:35:42.480
[Guest]: But my mom could not keep it inside and this is your third coming out of saying that, yeah.

00:35:42.480 --> 00:35:46.240
[Guest]: And this was the final official for me like being openly gay sort of thing.

00:35:46.240 --> 00:35:49.720
[Guest]: And I was like, the whole world knows, everybody knows, everybody's cool with it.

00:35:49.720 --> 00:35:51.040
[Amit Varma]: I just want you all to be okay with it.

00:35:51.040 --> 00:35:54.240
[Amit Varma]: And you've prepared them like first you're a writer, then you're an atheist and what

00:35:54.240 --> 00:36:00.280
[Guest]: can get worse and your dad is thinking it's okay, it can't get worse.

00:36:00.280 --> 00:36:04.400
[Guest]: And yeah, so like I was expecting my mom to not tell anybody and I remember it was a Monday.

00:36:04.400 --> 00:36:05.400
[Guest]: So we had Monday.

00:36:05.400 --> 00:36:06.660
[Amit Varma]: How did your mom react?

00:36:06.660 --> 00:36:07.660
[Guest]: So she was very chill.

00:36:07.660 --> 00:36:12.440
[Guest]: Like she just like, looked into the distance and like, I've heard about people.

00:36:12.440 --> 00:36:16.720
[Guest]: And she told me about one of her family relatives who was gay and married a woman and then would

00:36:16.720 --> 00:36:19.040
[Guest]: still go and have sex with men.

00:36:19.040 --> 00:36:22.800
[Guest]: And when his wife finally found out she lost her marbles, like she literally went insane.

00:36:22.800 --> 00:36:24.880
[Guest]: They had to put her in an asylum.

00:36:24.880 --> 00:36:27.160
[Guest]: And I was just like, do you want that future for me, mom?

00:36:27.160 --> 00:36:31.240
[Guest]: Because if I marry a woman tomorrow, as per your wishes, I'll end up like not satisfying

00:36:31.240 --> 00:36:35.200
[Guest]: her and she'll then like blame us and you know, all that racket.

00:36:35.200 --> 00:36:37.120
[Guest]: And a lot of people do live that lifestyle.

00:36:37.120 --> 00:36:42.120
[Guest]: And she was like, you know what, like, it's okay, I understand, I can live with the fact

00:36:42.120 --> 00:36:44.600
[Guest]: that there are people who are gay out there.

00:36:44.600 --> 00:36:48.600
[Guest]: But it's just difficult because I think you're my son and how will you lead a life like that?

00:36:48.600 --> 00:36:52.000
[Guest]: And that's why I was like, it's okay, because I've told a lot of people and they all chill

00:36:52.000 --> 00:36:55.160
[Guest]: with it and they're all like supporting and really understanding.

00:36:55.160 --> 00:36:57.440
[Guest]: I just want you all to be in my corner.

00:36:57.440 --> 00:36:59.920
[Guest]: But I think I don't know how she took it that night.

00:36:59.920 --> 00:37:03.960
[Guest]: She mulled over it because when I told her it was cool, because I went to an open mic

00:37:03.960 --> 00:37:07.680
[Guest]: directly after that moment, and I went and declared that open mic that for two years,

00:37:07.680 --> 00:37:10.080
[Guest]: I've been trying to come out to my family and tonight it actually happened.

00:37:10.080 --> 00:37:11.520
[Guest]: I have footage of that.

00:37:11.520 --> 00:37:13.240
[Guest]: And people were applauding and it was pretty good.

00:37:13.240 --> 00:37:14.440
[Guest]: Kanan Gill was hosting that night.

00:37:14.440 --> 00:37:15.440
[Guest]: He was really happy.

00:37:15.440 --> 00:37:19.920
[Guest]: Like he went and joked about how dreams come true at open mics and stuff like that.

00:37:19.920 --> 00:37:23.200
[Guest]: And it was a really positive moment in my life for a change.

00:37:23.200 --> 00:37:28.200
[Guest]: But the very next day, I felt like there was some amount of disdain in my house.

00:37:28.200 --> 00:37:32.640
[Guest]: The air hung very like serious and my mom and dad and my sister were both like staring

00:37:32.640 --> 00:37:37.640
[Guest]: at me with intense, like, you know, like, I actually went bald the same week I came

00:37:37.640 --> 00:37:41.920
[Guest]: out, which is not the smartest move because now they had two reasons to hate me.

00:37:41.920 --> 00:37:42.920
[Amit Varma]: Because I had like...

00:37:42.920 --> 00:37:43.920
[Amit Varma]: Well done.

00:37:43.920 --> 00:37:44.920
[Guest]: Tactically brilliant.

00:37:44.920 --> 00:37:48.840
[Guest]: At least my hair came back, I'm still gay that way.

00:37:48.840 --> 00:37:52.840
[Guest]: So so you know, they were like, not getting what I was trying to tell them.

00:37:52.840 --> 00:37:56.680
[Guest]: And then I called my friend who's also a gay activist.

00:37:56.680 --> 00:38:01.520
[Guest]: And he was like, if you want to come home and stay with us, you can sort the situation

00:38:01.520 --> 00:38:03.280
[Guest]: out, don't worry.

00:38:03.280 --> 00:38:06.000
[Guest]: But I would say stay back, talk to them.

00:38:06.000 --> 00:38:10.680
[Guest]: So this was from a Monday to Friday, it was just constant, you know, like, should I leave?

00:38:10.680 --> 00:38:11.680
[Guest]: Should I stay?

00:38:11.680 --> 00:38:12.680
[Amit Varma]: Should I leave?

00:38:12.680 --> 00:38:13.680
[Guest]: Should I stay?

00:38:13.680 --> 00:38:14.680
[Guest]: And how did your dad react?

00:38:14.680 --> 00:38:15.680
[Guest]: He was again stone cold.

